		<tr align="left" valign="top">
			<td class="BoardRowA">
			<a class="AuthorLink" href="/user.asp?usr=18903">Luck</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;			
			</td>
			<td class="BoardRowA">4/25/00 9:09am</td>
			<td class="BoardRowA"><a name="5509994"><span style="font-weight: bold;">
				EQ is NOT a ROLEPLAYING GAME
			</span></a></td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Yes, I know it says it is a roleplaying game.  And, yes I know there are many of you who want to roleplay in the game.  And yes, I know there are many who make valiant efforts at roleplaying their characters in the game.   <br>  <br> The problem with EQ is that the game just doesn't support roleplaying.  For true roleplaying there needs to be an interactive plot.  Players need to be able to make permanent changes within their world.  The environment needs to be ever changing and not static.  In EQ we simply do not find these things... and we never will unless there is a lot of new code written.  Let's face it, thats not going to happen. <br>  <br> I too, bought the game with high hopes of being able to roleplay.  I mean, it was advertised as a roleplaying game...geez.  Well, i had fun with the game for awhile but quickly grew bored, as the only real thing to do in the game is to try to level.  To do this requires fighting the same beasts over and over... ugh..it turned into such drudgery. <br>  <br> I had hopes for a time that Verant would add features to the game necessary to roleplaying.  But as time went by, and there were no changes, not even fixes to some very lame trades skills, I realized that this would not happen.  The only changes Verant is going to make is adding new zones, fixing minor technical bugs, and whatever else is necessary to keep the majority of the customers.  And this is somewhat understandable, they are a company in the business of making money.  I just wish they had never advertised the game as a ROLEPLAYING game.  Apparently they really have no idea what a roleplaying game is.  Just because it has some dragons, orcs, and elves many people will call it a roleplaying game...yeah, right. <br>  <br> This post is not meant to be against those who are currently trying to get a RPing server.  I wish you the best of luck.  I just don't have any faith in Verant to make the necessary changes to implement the idea.		

