		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				The problem with RP in EQ isn't all Verant's fault.  I'll admit that some of the choices they made with the game seem to favor the 'levelers' more than roleplay, BUT that is as much the players fault as it is Verant's.  People in this game choose to camp spawns, not because it's fun (most of them hate to camp for stuff).  You could easily have a few groups meet at the entrance to Unrest and 'raid' the house.  But because a group of people decide &quot;I MUST have dwarven work boots! and I'm not leaving until I do!&quot; and go sit in that room, they ruin the opportunity for roleplay, because they remove the goal of the dungeon. <br> Yes, it IS Verant's fault that they CAN do that by making the spawn repetative (every 20 minutes or whatever it is for the ghost), and by making it so that high level people can just walk past the lower level mobs without a care.  BUT, it is still the PLAYER's fault for actually going and DOING the camping. <br>  <br> But then again, there is more to 'roleplay' than running around with a funny accent and all that.  If you have a cleric in your group that won't heal people, kick him out, because he's not playing his role (roleplaying).  :)		

