			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				I do think EQ is a roll playing game.  When you play a traditional RPing game such as D&amp;D do you just sit there and let the DM tell you a story? No you don't. You interact and do things to. The DM only keeps you guided and keep a story going. <br>  <br> In EQ you can still RP, yes you can't make big changes to the world but you, as a player can still interact with other players to form storys of their relation ships since you can't go have a conversation with Antonius Bayle or slay the king of Ak'Anon for good. <br>  <br> Someone wrote a pretty good editorial on Everquest Express in issue 120 or 121. I recomend you check it out if you have never read it.		

