			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Again, don't misunderstand what I am saying.  I am not saying it is impossible to roleplay in EQ, i am only saying that the atmosphere of the game is not condusive to this type of play. And yes, this is Verant's fault.  Sure players can choose to ignore the faults, but the fact is that people will play the game as it has been written..and it hasn't been written to support roleplaying. <br>  <br> And roleplaying does of course mean interaction with other players but it also means interaction with monsters and your surrounding environment.  If for example, I tried to roleplay a loner who by nature seldom speaks or involves himself with others this would be nearly impossible since I would get no interation from the environment. This is just one example of hundreds I could think of... There are ways to roleplay in the game, but these are very contrived.   <br>  <br> 		

