			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				IMO... <br> its both verant AND players fault. <br> To me, the &quot;dynamic quests&quot; which were suppose to add to the element of RPing has become nothing more than &quot;give me a magic item!&quot; <br> noone even cares for the story, they just want an item.I've seen lv 50s complain about having &quot;weak&quot; items being dropped off of a dynamic quest mob... The problem doesnt stem here, its in the whole atmosphere of the game. It seems that 90% of the people who play EQ are indeed, playing to get the best item, get the highest level, be the best that you can be, and say screw everyone else-I'm playing the game for ME. <br> And Verant is at fault for promoting this by having special mobs drop special items, not going to the randomizing that Asherons Call(AC) because they feel &quot;its against what we envisioned the game to be.&quot; They also allow some classes to be able to solo lv 50 creatures while the rest of us (I'm play a paladin as my prime char) get our arses handed to us. <br> I always get a kicker out of their &quot;envision&quot; excuse... <br> What do they envision? i often wonder... <br> because the reality is that high lv dungeons (such as SolB and LG) are OVERCROWDED with 80 people in LG and 50 people in SolB on good nights. <br> Thankfully we have Kunark to ease the conjusted zones but it still doesnt promote Rping. <br> The best thing about Kunark is exploring new territory that noone else has seen-temporarily having the powergamers/item farmers crawl out of their hole and play the game as what it was meant to be-exploration and adventure.(IMO anyways) But after they done that, its back to playing the game as how they see it-just kill and get an item. <br>  <br> EQ can be fun to rp, just need to get those kinds of people together under one roof and get a story going =) <br>  <br> Plus if you want a REAL rping game, check out NeverwinterNights , it'll be out in some time, but it looks great =)  <br>  <br>  <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://neverwinternights.com/">http://neverwinternights.com/</a>  <br>   <br> 		

