			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				EQ is NOT a ROLEPLAYING GAME <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br> ......... <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br>  <br> EQ is NOT a LEVELING GAME <br>  <br>  <br> Eq doesn't favor either leveling or roleplaying. As hard as it is to belive- you can roleplay without leveling. Want to travel? Roleplay a shadow knight(or some other tricky or evil class- get a wizard and trick the wizard into teleporting you someplace and make a run for it. <br>  <br> SK: Hey can you teleport? <br> WIZ: Why yes I can. <br> SK: Can you teleport me? <br> WIZ: No, I'm not teleporting now. <br> SK: Hmph! I bet you don't even know teleport. <br> WIZ: Yes, I do! <br> Sk: No you're too weak to teleport. <br> WIZ: Fine, I'll teleport myself somewhere. <br> SK: How do I know you teleported? Maybe you just cast invisable or camoflauge on yourself. <br> WIZ: Fine, I'll take you with me just to prove it. <br>  <br> This is kind of a lame example but do you see where I am getting at. EQ is a freestyle game, do whatever you want- want to make items? Take up a trade skill. Want to be the best fighter? Then go level. Want to roleplay? Then go ahead, ROLEPLAY! The only people that ruin roleplaying are the people that say EQ is not a RPG. If they don't think that roleplaying is found on EQ then just don't say anything. Go level or camp or whatever you want to do just don't interfere with people that are acually trying to roleplay! <br>  <br> Well sorry if it sounded like I was flaming but I just see alot of these &quot;EQ not RPG!&quot; that I got annoyed. <br>  <br> Mr. Boombastic <br> &quot;If you want to rplay a hot wood elf stripper- don't let me stop you!&quot;		

